content.description: The first pitch is nothing to write home about but the 2nd pitch is an aesthetic hands splitter through an open face in a hugh right facing dihedral.  It's hard to be sure but I believe a third pitch to the rim does exist.
content.protection: A few odds and ends for the first pitch then nothing but hand sized gear for the 2nd.  Bolted belay anchors.
content.location: Located on the right side of the southern buttress.

content.description: A manky 1st pitch leads to a wide fingers splitter in a huge right facing corner.
content.protection: Fingers to hands (a few of each). Bolted belay anchors.
content.location: Located on the right side of the southern buttress.

content.description: Hands to off-width arching right on beautiful desert varnished stone.
content.protection: A few hand and OW pieces
content.location: Roughly the center of the southern buttress (easy to spot).

content.description: This is a very aesthetic line cutting diagonally across the face of a large detached pillar on the northern buttress.   Hands to thin hands.
content.protection: A few of each hand size, save a .75 for the top.
content.location: This route is located on the south face of the big detached pillar.

content.description: Good hands in a right facing corner... needs a belay anchor at the top of the 1st pitch.
content.location: This route is located on the right side of the northern buttress.

content.description: A runout start brings you to fingers in a right facing corner with an excellent thin hands above. The 2nd pitch is of less quality and tops out but there is a bolted anchor at the top of the 1st pitch (30m).
content.protection: Mostly thin fingers to hand sized gear but bring some bigger gear if climbing the 2nd pitch.
content.location: This route is located left of the large detached pillar on the northern buttress.

content.description: This is a short thin hands crack with a funky start.  Optional 2nd pitch to the top.
content.protection: A couple of each: finger, thin hands and hands. Save a .75 for the top.
content.location: This one is easy to spot, it's located on the east face of the large detached pillar, right of 'Sun Dawg'.
